    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="252"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Ambassador in
                        the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d252fn1">Sent by the United States Naval
                        Attaché, Moscow, via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Excerpts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-11">11 October
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 83. Top Secret and Personal. From the President for Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Regarding our war plans for the Pacific, I understand that <persName
                        corresp="#p_D1">Deane</persName> has all the information as to American
                    plans that are available and that he has given, or will give, this information
                    to the Soviet Staff.</p>
                <p>If <persName corresp="#p_D1">Deane</persName> has already informed the Soviet
                    Staff and unless <persName corresp="#p_D1">Deane</persName> should consider it
                    inadvisable at the present time, I have no objection to your giving this
                    information to <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> .</p>
                <p>You are correct in assuming that the Pacific campaign will remain an American
                    command and there is no objection to <persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        >Churchill</persName>’s informing the Soviet that the British Fleet and
                    British Land and Air Forces will participate in those areas, at present
                    undetermined, where their services will be of the greatest value to the war
                    against Japan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
